{
  "texts": [
    "Since the first computers debuted in the 1950s (Boukhari, 2021), artificial intelligence (AI) has undergone a second renaissance.",
    "It is all down to the explosion of available data and computing power, and it has enabled the creation of computational (algorithmic) models that can detect trends and adjust on the fly by computer scientists.",
    "Artificial intelligence applications are employed more often in fields and contexts besides computing.",
    "Smartphones, recommendation engines, and support desks all fall under this heading (Choudrie et al., 2023) (Adwan et al., 2022).",
    "Journalists, artists, musicians, and marketers, all fields formerly assumed to require human intelligence, now see AI assuming increasingly sophisticated roles (Alaql et al., 2023)."
  ]
}